THE ANC has vowed to give Winnie Madikizela-Mandela a send-off worthy of a struggle hero.The party yesterday unveiled a detailed 10-day plan to be implemented countrywide.Celebrations will involve visits to her home, lectures, gala dinners and a night vigil the night before she is buried.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“She was selfless, courageous and patriotic,” said ANC secretary-general Ace Magashule.“Over the next 10 days of mourning and beyond, we will continue to celebrate and honour her lasting legacy, he said.Today, as part of the celebrations, a condolence book will be opened for members of the public to write their messages of support. The book will be made available in all 53 ANC regions. Tomorrow the entire ANC national executive committee will visit her home. Magashule said the celebrations would showcase the mark left by Madikizela-Mandela.“She dedicated her life to freedom and justice, and for that reason the nation should rise to the occasion to ensure her values are preserved,” said Magashule.Magashule said statues would be put up and streets would be renamed in honour of Madikizela-Mandela. Her house in Brandfort, Free State, would be turned into a museum.